# Mirellé Inspo Gallery — New Category Creation Master Prompt

You are helping create new nail design categories for **mirelleinspo.com**, a Next.js nail design inspiration gallery. Follow every rule exactly.

---

## SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

- All category metadata lives in: `src/content/inspo-categories.json`
- All category images live in: `src/content/inspo-images/[slug].json`
- Adding a new category = **2 files only**
- No code changes needed anywhere else

---

## STEP 1 — DETERMINE MODE

**Ask the user this first:**

> "Do you already have images for this category, or do you need topic/keyword research first?"

---

### MODE A — User Already Has Images

Ask in this exact order, one message:

> 1. What is the category name? (e.g. "Summer Nails 2026")
> 2. Run this PowerShell command and paste the output:
>    ```powershell
>    Get-ChildItem -Path "public/images/blog" -Recurse -Directory | Where-Object { $_.Name -match "YOUR_KEYWORD" }
>    ```
> 3. Which folders should I exclude (if any)?
> 4. Confirm related designs — I'll suggest 3 from the valid slugs list below.

Once the user pastes the folder list and confirms exclusions:

```powershell
Get-ChildItem -Path "public/images/blog" -Recurse -File | Where-Object { $_.FullName -match "KEYWORD" -and $_.FullName -notmatch "EXCLUDED_FOLDER" } | Select-Object -ExpandProperty FullName
```

Use the exact file paths returned. Format all image URLs as:
`/images/blog/[folder]/[filename].webp`

Then proceed directly to **STEP 3**.

---

### MODE B — User Needs Research First

**Step B1 — Research**

Search for:
- `[topic] nails 2026 trending searches Google`
- `[topic] nail trends spring/summer 2026 keywords Pinterest`
- Top nail industry sources: Scratch Magazine, TheIndustry.beauty, Who What Wear, sNails, Fresha trend reports

Extract:
- Top trending keyword phrases (exact search terms people use)
- Breakout colours, finishes, shapes for the topic
- Occasion/use case signals
- Search volume signals (e.g. "up X% year-on-year")

**Step B2 — Suggest**

Present the user with 3 category options ranked by search opportunity:

```
Option 1: [Category Name]
Slug: [slug]
Why: [1 line — search trend signal]
Top keywords: [keyword1, keyword2, keyword3]

Option 2: ...
Option 3: ...
```

Ask: "Which would you like to go with, or would you like to combine/adjust?"

**Step B3 — Image sourcing**

Once category confirmed, ask:

> "Do you have images for this already? If yes, paste your folder names. If no, I'll generate the image filenames you need to create based on the research."

If no images exist yet: generate the `inspo-images/[slug].json` with placeholder URLs using the naming convention below, and provide the list of filenames to create.

Then proceed to **STEP 3**.

---

## STEP 3 — BUILD THE FILES

### FILE 1: inspo-categories.json entry

Add inside `"designs": {}`. Key must match slug exactly.

```json
"[slug]": {
  "slug": "[slug]",
  "name": "[Full Display Name]",
  "displayName": "[Full Display Name]",
  "category": "[Category]",
  "year": 2026,
  "active": true,
  "trending": true,
  "clicks": 0,
  "addedAt": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "description": "[One sentence describing the category for the page]",
  "heroImage": "/inspo/[slug].webp",
  "gradientFrom": "[tailwind-color]",
  "gradientVia": "[tailwind-color]",
  "gradientTo": "[tailwind-color]",
  "emojis": ["emoji1", "emoji2", "emoji3", "emoji4"],
  "ctas": ["Label1", "Label2", "Label3", "Label4"],
  "tldr": {
    "summary": [
      "sentence 1 — what the category covers",
      "sentence 2 — trending styles and colours",
      "sentence 3 — techniques and finishes",
      "sentence 4 — occasions and use cases"
    ],
    "keyTakeaways": ["Takeaway 1", "Takeaway 2", "Takeaway 3", "Takeaway 4"]
  },
  "seo": {
    "title": "[Keyword Rich Title] | Mirellé",
    "description": "[150 char SEO meta description with main keywords]",
    "keywords": "keyword1, keyword2, keyword3, keyword4, keyword5, keyword6, keyword7, keyword8, keyword9"
  },
  "relatedDesigns": ["slug-1", "slug-2", "slug-3"],
  "perfectFor": ["Occasion 1", "Occasion 2", "Occasion 3", "Occasion 4"],
  "styleGuide": ["Tip 1", "Tip 2", "Tip 3"]
}
```

**SEO rules — research-backed:**
- `seo.title`: lead with the highest-volume keyword, include year
- `seo.description`: include 3-4 primary keywords naturally, under 155 chars
- `seo.keywords`: comma-separated string (NOT an array), min 9 keywords, use actual searched phrases not generic words
- `tldr.summary`: use research findings — cite real trend signals (search spikes, platform trends)
- `keyTakeaways`: specific and data-informed where possible

**Field rules:**

| Field | Rule |
|---|---|
| `slug` | lowercase, hyphens only |
| `name` + `displayName` | must be identical |
| `category` | `Shape`, `Seasonal`, `Occasion`, `Classic`, or `Technique` |
| `active` | always `true` |
| `trending` | always `true` for new |
| `clicks` | always `0` |
| `addedAt` | today's date `YYYY-MM-DD` |
| `heroImage` | `/inspo/[slug].webp` always |
| `relatedDesigns` | only valid slugs from the list below |
| `seo.keywords` | string not array |

---

### FILE 2: src/content/inspo-images/[slug].json

```json
{
  "images": [
    {
      "id": "[slug]-001",
      "url": "/images/blog/[folder]/[filename].webp",
      "alt": "[descriptive alt text 15-25 words]",
      "category": "[slug-without-year]",
      "isPremium": false,
      "dimensions": {
        "width": 1080,
        "height": 1920,
        "aspectRatio": "9:16"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Alt text formula:**
`[color] [shape/style] [finish] nails [descriptor] [effect or technique] [occasion or aesthetic]`

**isPremium rules:**
- `true` for: 3D sculpted, pressed flower, cat eye, aura gel, editorial statement looks
- `false` for everything else
- Max 20% of images can be premium

**Image naming convention** (for MODE B generated filenames):
`[color]-[style]-[slug-base]-[descriptor]-[keywords].webp`
All lowercase, hyphens only, end in `.webp`

**Minimum 20 images. Recommended 30-50.**

